=== Viswanathan Anand (2000, 2008 and 2012) ===
In 2000, when Karpov, Korchnoi and Kasparov were still active, [[Viswanathan Anand|Anand]] listed his top 10 as: [[Bobby Fischer|Fischer]], [[Paul Morphy|Morphy]], [[Emanuel Lasker|Lasker]], [[Jos? Ra?l Capablanca|Capablanca]], [[Wilhelm Steinitz|Steinitz]], [[Mikhail Tal|Tal]], [[Viktor Korchnoi|Korchnoi]], [[Paul Keres|Keres]], [[Anatoly Karpov|Karpov]] and [[Garry Kasparov|Kasparov]].<ref>[http://in.rediff.com/millenni/anand.htm The Grandmaster on his ten greatest chess players], [[Viswanathan Anand]], rediff.com</ref>

When interviewed in 2008 shortly after Fischer's death, he ranked Fischer and Kasparov as the greatest with Kasparov a little ahead by virtue of being on top for many years.<ref>"''He (Fischer) and Kasparov were the greatest in history, but I judge Kasparov as a little ahead. Fischer was a phenomenon from 1970 to 1972 while Kasparov was on top for many years.''" ? [http://www.chessbase.com/newsprint.asp?newsid=4450 Morelia-Linares Super-GM starts today], [[Chessbase]], 15 February 2008</ref>

In 2012, Anand stated that he considered Fischer as the greatest on account of the hurdles he faced.<ref>[http://www.thehindu.com/sport/other-sports/article3486974.ece Anand takes a dig at Kasparov], [[Viswanathan Anand]], The Hindu</ref>

